Glossary of terms and additional information

LOS - Line of Sight

GW - Groundwave (station is normally receivable on a regular basis)

Tr - Tropospheric Ducting

Ms - Meteor scatter

TrS - Troposcatter

Es - Sporadic E-Skip

Stations indicated with after the city of TX were received on the date indicated.

Receptions in St. Cloud are made with a variety of radios, more than likely a Sony XDR-F1HD, Grundig S350, Grundig G8, or the stock radio of a 2010 Subaru Impreza (Outback edition) with RDS. For weather radio, a police scanner - Radioshack Pro-528 is used.

Note - any time you see the word (Stale) whether it includes Stale Tr, or Stale Es, for example, it means the station was logged on a previous day (or more) and wasn't updated until after the fact. These are then counted among the newer logs. I try and update the log each time I get new stations but I am only human, and get behind like everyone else. Plus, other matters may interfere with updating the logs that I can't forsee.

~ - rough distance measurement +/- 10-30 miles.
